name: ICCameraFile
desc: An object that represents a file on a camera.

items.name: originalFilename
items.desc: The original name of the file on disk.

items.name: createdFilename
items.desc: The created name of the file.

items.name: groupUUID
items.desc: The group UUID of the file.

items.name: relatedUUID
items.desc: A related UUID correlating several images from an Apple device.

items.name: originatingAssetID
items.desc: The originating asset ID of an HEIF or HVEC file.

items.name: fileCreationDate
items.desc: The creation date of the file.

items.name: fileModificationDate
items.desc: The modification date of the file.

items.name: fileSize
items.desc: The size of the file, in bytes.

items.name: width
items.desc: The width of an image or movie frame.

items.name: height
items.desc: The height of an image or movie frame.

items.name: orientation
items.desc: The orientation to use when downloading the image.

items.name: ICEXIFOrientationType
items.desc: The fileâ€™s orientation type.

items.name: exifCreationDate
items.desc: The EXIF creation date of the file.

items.name: exifModificationDate
items.desc: The EXIF modification date of the file.

items.name: gpsString
items.desc: The GPS String of the file in standard format.

items.name: firstPicked
items.desc: A Boolean value that indicates whether a file is autopicked by Photos to represent the burst.

items.name: burstUUID
items.desc: The burst UUID of the file if it is in a burst.

items.name: burstFavorite
items.desc: A Boolean value that indicates this file is the burst favorite in a burst.

items.name: burstPicked
items.desc: A Boolean value that indicates whether this file is user picked in a burst.

items.name: duration
items.desc: The duration, in seconds, of an audio or video file.

items.name: highFramerate
items.desc: A Boolean value that indicates whether the file is a slow motion or high-frame-rate video file.

items.name: timeLapse
items.desc: A Boolean value that indicates whether the file is a time-lapse video file.

items.name: sidecarFiles
items.desc: An array of two camera files associated with this file.

items.name: pairedRawImage
items.desc: A sidecar file containing the logical RAW compliment of a JPG or other two-format image.
